data.message: Hi family and friends! This year I will be participating with the Sigma Kappa Alpha Mu chapter in the Walk to End Alzheimer's on October 8th in Ann Arbor! Alzheimer's affects 1 in 3 seniors in the U.S. and is currently the 6th most likely cause of death. The disease has affected millions of families as both a financial and emotional burden, and I am walking to find a cure! The money donated will be put towards Alzheimer's research in order to end the disease. Any and all donations are appreciated, thank you!

data.message:
Hi all!
My sorority, Sigma Kappa, is participating in an event this weekend called Winterfest, an annual philanthropy event hosted by the Alpha Sigma Phi and Pi Kappa Alpha fraternities at the University of Michigan. Thousands of people come throughout the day every year to watch a greek life broomball tournament on an ice rink constructed by the brothers of the fraternity. 
The proceeds of the event will be supporting the Autism Alliance of Michigan which is a non-profit organization who's mission is to lead unprecedented collaboration that will improve the quality of life for individuals with autism and their loved ones through education, comprehensive services, coordinated advocacy, dedication to community, and navigation.
Please consider donating to this awesome cause that means a lot to me and the community!!
